US-based music promotion company,  Sammek Moments Arts and Cultural Entertainment, is organising a tour of different cities for music band  Saxtee Vibes. The musical tour of many states in the U.S. has brought excitement to the group led by talented  saxophonist and instrumentalist, Babatunde Balogun.   Sanwo-Olu desires to transform film industry in Lagos, says…     Erigga: No girl should be given Valentine’s gift…     How I was almost pushed to quit acting – Moyo Lawal   According to a statement from the music company owned by Samuel Ekundayo, Saxtee Vibes will be in the United States to display their uniquely combined talents as a team. “The first leg of the musical tour will see Balogun and his band, Saxtee Vibes perform dexterously at the events and carnivals that include Alujo Nite at Atlanta Event Centre Opera, Annual AHBCA Award at Expo Event Centre, Houston, Texas; Ijoko Agba Nite at Kings Banquet Hall, Milwaukee, Ankara Nite in Texas, and the Annual Yoruba Cultural Festival in Howell, Miami.” Balogun, an indigene of Ondo state, has been on the music scene for close to 25 years now, and he has taken his musical prowess and band to different countries. He has also toured and performed on the same stage with veteran Nigerian musicians like Evangelist Ebenezer Obey, King Sunny Ade, Sir Shina Peters, King Wasiu Ayinde, Queen Ayo Balogun, and Adewale Ayuba.